node.text:
@USANAinc Active Nutrition is here!!🥳 this Electrolyte Replacement is part of it and essential for the summer heat. .Sponsored 

Dressing
* 3 tbsp olive oil
* 3 tbsp lime juice
* 3 garlic clove, minced
* 2 packets Electrolyte Replacement
For the salad
* 5 cups cubed watermelon 
* 1/4 cup Blueberries
* 1/3 Cup Cucumbers
* 1 medium Avocado, cubed 
* 1/2 Serrano Pepper, sliced
* 2 oz. Feta Cheese, crumbled
* mint to taste
* Sea salt and pepper to taste 
Instructions:
Now let’s get started. First whisk together all dressing ingredients. Set aside. 
Assemble the salad ingredients on a platter as desired. Feel free to add or substitute ingredients as you like! Season to taste and serve with dressing. Perfect for the summer!#LiveUSANA  #USANAactive #salad #summer #watermelon #hydrate

node.title: Watermelon Salad with hydrating watermelon dressing 🥗🍉

- 50 g (1/2 cup) oat flour (or rolled oats)
- 100 ml (1/3 cup 1 tbsp) nondairy milk
- 15 g (1 tbsp) maple syrup (or preferred sweetener)
- 15g peanut butter 
- 10g cocoa powder
- 10g (1 square) melted chocolate
- 1/2 tsp baking powder
- 1 chocolate square
Directions⏱ 
- Heat oven to 180 Cº (360 Fº).
- If using rolled oats, blend oats into flour.
- In a bowl mash 1/2 banana and combine with oat flour, cocoa powder, maple syrup, 1 melted chocolate square and baking powder. 
- Transfer to an ovenproof bowl 3/4 batter, add peanut butter & chocolate in the center and cover with the remaining batter. Top with more peanut butter.
- Bake for 20/25 minutes.

Deutsch 🇩🇪 
- 1/2 banane
- 50g Hafermehl
- 100ml Milch (vegan)
- 15g Süßungmittel (Ahornsyrup)
- 15g Erdnussbutter 
- 10g Kakaopulver 
- 10g geschmolzene Schokolade 
- 2.5g Backpulver
- 10g Schokolade 
Anleitung ⏱ 
- In eine Schale 1/2 gestampfte Banane, Hafermehl, Kakaopulver, Süßungmittel, Backpulver, geschmolzene Schokolade, Milch zugeben und mischen. 
- Den Teig in eine oven Bachform zugeben, die Erdnussbutter und Schokolade ins Zentrum hinzufügen. Mit etwa mehr Teig bedecken und mit Erdnussbutter dekorieren.
- In heißen Oven auf 180 Cº für ca. 20/25 Minuten backen.

node.text:
Orecchiette with Sausage and Broccoli
-
A super simple recipe that uses minimal ingredients by @cookingclassy 🥦 
It’s packs rich, savory, satisfying flavors. It includes hearty pasta, seasoned Italian sausage, tender fresh broccoli, flavorful olive oil, and bold and nutty tasting parmesan.

1 lb broccoli crowns, bottom stalk trimmed and reserved for another use, remaining cut into florets
Salt and freshly ground black pepper
12 oz. orecchiette pasta
4 Tbsp extra-virgin olive oil, divided, plus more if desired
1 1/2 Tbsp minced garlic (4 cloves)
1 lb Italian sausage* (can use mild or hot)
2/3 cup (1.6 oz) finely shredded Parmesan, plus more for serving
1 1/2 cups reserved pasta water, divided
Red pepper flakes, for serving
Instructions

Add 4 quarts of water to a large pot, bring to a boil over medium-high heat then season with salt (I use 2 Tbsp).
Add broccoli to boiling water and cook until tender, about 4 - 5 minutes. Using a spider, remove broccoli and transfer to a colander, while leaving water in pot.
Run broccoli under cold water to stop cooking. Drain well. Chop broccoli into smaller pieces.
Add pasta to water in pot and boil about 1 minutes shy of al dente, according to time listed on package. Reserve 1 1/2 cups pasta water.
While pasta is boiling, heat 1 Tbsp olive oil into a 12-inch non-stick skillet over medium-high heat.
Crumble sausage in small chunks into skillet and cook, breaking up and tossing occasionally, until cooked through, about 7 minutes. Add garlic during last 2 minutes of cooking the sausage.
Pour in 1 cup of the pasta water into the sausage. Let it simmer for about a minute and reduce slightly. Add all dente pasta and cook while tossing, until tender, about 2 minutes.
Drizzle in remaining 3 Tbsp olive oil, season with red pepper flakes to taste and toss.
Sprinkle in parmesan, and toss to melt into sauce.
Toss in broccoli. Season with salt as needed and pepper to taste.
Loosen with more pasta water as needed. Drizzle servings with more olive oil if desired, serve with garnished with more parmesan.

node.text:
Easy Chocolate Chip Banana Bread, the perfect classic banana bread recipe!! 
By @wellnessbykay

It’s super moist, deliciously soft, and absolutely loaded with chocolate chips. plus it’s super easy to make ... you only need one bowl, no hand mixer, and 15 minutes of prep time.  so good !! hope you all love this one as much as i do 🤍✨ 
1 1/2 cups mashed ripe bananas (about 4 bananas)
1/2 cup coconut sugar
1/2 cup salted butter, melted
2 eggs
2 tsp vanilla extract
1 1/4 cup all purpose flour
2 tsp baking powder
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 cup semi sweet mini chocolate chips
INSTRUCTIONS

Set the oven to 350 degrees.
Next in a large mixing bowl mash your ripe bananas.
Add in the melted butter, coconut sugar, eggs, and vanilla extract.  Combine until smooth.
Then add the all purpose flour, baking powder, and salt and combine evenly.
Stir in the chocolate chips.
Transfer to a greased or parchment paper lined loaf tin.  Top with extra chocolate chips and a sprinkle of salt.
Bake for 50 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Let cool, cut into slices, and enjoy!

node.text:
Grilled Corn & Avocado Tomato Salad

#Ad One of my favorite summer salads! It is super flavorful, filling, and you can include all the summer veggie favorites! 🌽🍅🥑 I’m excited to partner with Reynolds Wrap® for this post. I used Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil from @ReynoldsBrands to grill the ears of corn. I love that Reynolds Wrap foil is durable and sturdy, perfect to use when cooking on the grill. The foil traps in the steam and juices, and keeps the corn from drying out so there’s no need to pre-soak it. Reynolds Wrap® now has a new box that is easier to open and comes with a tab that keeps the box fully closed when you store it. The new boxes are also color-coded by type. For Heavy Duty Foil, look for the box with the light blue end.
 
Ingredients
5 ears of fresh corn
5 pieces of @ReynoldsBrands Reynolds Wrap® Heavy Duty Foil cut in 16” pieces
2 avocados - peeled, pitted and diced
1/2 small red onion, sliced into strips
12 oz cherry tomatoes on the vine, sliced in halves or quarters depending on size
1/2 serrano pepper, sliced (optional)
Juice of a lime
Baby arugula
For this recipe, turn the grill on high heat. While the grill heats, prepare the corn. Start by shucking the corn and remove all the silk.
Lay out 5 pieces of foil approximately 16” for each cob of corn. Stack the foil and work from the top, one at a time. Place a corn cob in the center on each piece of foil and wrap each cob in the foil, like a present. Fold at the top leaving space for the heat to circulate. Then, tightly seal the ends by double folding.
Place the foil-wrapped corn on the grill and close the lid. Grill over high heat for 10-15 minutes, turning once. You want the corn to be tender but not soft!
While the corn is cooking, prepare the remaining salad ingredients.
After the corn cooks, remove it from the grill and allow it to cool until it’s easy to handle.
Continue preparing the remaining ingredients. Once you have finished the preparation work and the corn is cool, unwrap them.
Cut the corn off the cob. Place all of the ingredients in a bowl. Mix gently and serve with your favorite dressing!
Enjoy!

node.text:
CHOCOLATE AVOCADO CHEESECAKE SQUARES 🥑🍫
no bake, gluten-free, vegan, oil & sugar-free 
By @kitchen_by_elle

SWIPE for the texture…

Such a simple recipe and made with only the best ingredients. I am absolutely thrilled to use avocado even for sweet dishes. Never thought it would taste so incredibly delicious. Be sure to give it a try. 🤍

Cream: 🥑
1 avocado 
1/2 lemon 
6 dates 
2 tablespoons cocoa
1 tablespoon maple 
50g cream cheese

Base: 🍫
100g rolled oats 
10g almond paste 
6 dates 
1 tablespoon cocoa 
a little water

Recipe:
1. put ingredients for the cream in the blender until everything is well mixed
2. mix ingredients for the base & put the mixture into a baking dish with baking paper and press it down
3. lift cream on top and then chill & enjoy

_________________________

So ein einfaches Rezept und nur aus den besten  Zutaten. Ich bin absolut begeistert Avocado auch für süße Gerichte zu verwenden. Hätte niemals gedacht, dass das so unfassbar lecker schmeckt. Probiert es unbedingt aus. 🤍

Creme: 🥑
1 Avocado 
1/2 Zitrone 
6 Datteln 
2 EL Kakao
1 EL Ahorn 
50g Frischkäse

Boden: 🍫
100 g Haferflocken 
10g Mandelmus 
6 Datteln 
1 EL Kakao 
etwas Wasser

Rezept:
1. Zutaten für die Creme in den Mixer geben, bis alles gut vermischt ist 
2. Zutaten für den Boden vermixen & die Masse in eine Auflaufform mit Backpapier geben und festdrücken
3. Creme oben drauf heben und dann kalt stellen & genießen

node.text:
Cookie dough ice cream (dairy-free) 🥛 🍪 Happy Sunday! By @wholesomehedonista 

Cookie Dough 
1/4 cup salted nut butter (I prefer peanut butter or cashew butter, or you can use almond butter if you like!) 
2 tablespoons maple syrup 
1 tsp vanilla (sorry forgot to film!)
1/4 cup almond flour 
1 tablespoon coconut flour
Mini chocolate chips 

Mix nut butter, maple syrup, and vanilla together in a small bowl until smooth. Stir in almond flour and coconut flour until a thick dough forms. Stir in chocolate chips. Roll into small balls and place in freezer until firm.

Ice cream:
1 can coconut milk or cream* (I used Thai kitchen coconut milk because it has mostly cream and very little water and a neutral flavor - if using a different brand go with coconut cream or chill can and scoop out thick white cream on top it should be 1 cup of thick cream total) 
1/4 cup maple syrup 
1/4 cup cashew butter
1 tsp vanilla 

Blend everything together until smooth. Pour into an ice cube tray. Freeze overnight until solid. Place ice cream cubes In a high powered blender with 2 tablespoons to 1/4 cup almond milk and blend until smooth, stopping blender to scrape down sides or using a tamper. Stir in cookie dough. Enjoy as soft serve right away or chill for a couple hours for more scoop-able firm texture. Hope you love it! 

#nicecream #cookiedoughicecream #cookiedough #vegandessert #dairyfree #vegan #veganicecream #dairyfreeicecream #coconutmilkicecream #paleo #veganglutenfree

🤗🎉 cheers to the weekend! 🙌🏻 today is another gorgeous day! Which is your favorite? All by @hellohealthyeating 

I’m craving a little bit of everything for breakfast 💕 #whatsonmyplate 1,2,3,or4?

1️⃣A slice of gfree toast- half with Pb + maple cream & half with avo 🍁🥑 + a bunch of fresh fruit & an egg/ brekkie sausage scramble 😋 I always make sure my breakfast includes a good mix of satisfying protein, energizing carbs & healthy fats to keep me fueled and focused for the morning!! 💫 ✨ #nourishplate #balance 
2️⃣a fruit salad, a slice of gfree toast with butter & a mini omelette + coffee on the side 💁🏼‍♀️ yum! 💕🎉 #nourishment #brunch
3️⃣sweet & savory style! ✨ English muffin 💕, a fried egg & some fresh fruit!! Simple & satisfying ☀️ ❤️🎉 #toasttuesday
4️⃣gfree toast with mashed avo, sea salt+ pepper & a fried egg 🥑🍞🍳 plus (of course) some coffee on the side! 🎉 #toasttuesday #balance
